{"word":"οὐ 13","slug":"οὐ 13","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n75881\" key=\"ou)13\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">οὐ μὲν οὖν</orth> or <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">οὐμενοῦν</orth>, <sense id=\"n75881.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">on the contrary . . not</tr_>. . , introducing a neg. statement in contradiction or correction of a preceding statement or suggestion, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg011.perseus-grc1:870\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">870</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg009.perseus-grc1:556\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ra.\">Ra.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">556</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg009.perseus-grc1:1188\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1188</biblScope> </bibl> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">οὐδενὸς μὲν οὖν ἄξιον</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg021:305a\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Euthd.\">Euthd.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">305a</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐγώ σοι οὐκ ἂν δυναίμην ἀντιλέγειν</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">;</tr_> Answ. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οὐ μὲν οὖν τῇ ἀληθείᾳ δύνασαι ἀντιλέγειν</foreign> nay it is <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">not me, but rather</tr_> truth, that you cannot gainsay, <bibl